5 November 2009Government Spokesperson, Themba Maseko, will brief the media tomorrow on the outcomes of today s Cabinet meeting held at Tuynhuys, Cape Town.He will be joined by the Defence and Military Veterans Minister, Lindiwe Sisulu, and the Water and Environmental Affairs Minister, Buyelwa Sonjica. The Ministers will provide more details on matters surrounding the Airbus A400M aircraft and climate change.The briefing will take place as follows:Date: 5 November (Thursday) Time: 11:00 Venue: Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Cape TownThere will be a video link to room 153, Union Buildings, PretoriaEnquiries: Colin Cruywagen (Cape Town) Cell: 082 377 9916Bongiwe Gambu (Pretoria) Cell: 082 714 9463Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)